The paper deals with the complexity of computing the simulation preorder of finite transition systems, which is a problem in model checking of temporal logic. This problem is related to variants of matrix multiplication, and the paper presents reductions and algorithms that use matrix multiplication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
